ValeciumOS Global Licensing Declaration and Policy
==================================================

This repository utilizes a multi-licensed architecture to govern the various
functional layers of the system. This policy ensures the project remains 
open-source while protecting the foundational identity of the OS.

License to specific files are all according to the SPDX License Identifier
labeled at the top of each file, and license text can be found in directory
`LICENCES/` within this repository.

1. GLOBAL FALLBACK LICENSE
--------------------------
Unless otherwise specified within a file header or categorized below, all 
source code, build scripts (SCons), and tools in this repository are 
governed by:

    - License: BSD 3-Clause "New" or "Revised" License
    - SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause
    - Full Text: LICENSES/BSD-3-Clause.txt

2. COMPONENT-SPECIFIC LICENSES
------------------------------
The following directories are subject to specific licensing terms that 
override the global fallback:

- `kernel/` (The Valecium Kernel)
    - SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0-only
    - Full Text: LICENSES/GPL-3.0.txt

- `Documentation/` (Project Manuals and Text)
    - SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-SA-4.0
    - Full Text: LICENSES/CC-BY-SA-4.0.txt

- `Documentation/assets/` (Icon, Logos, and Branding)
    - SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-SA-4.0
    - Full Text: LICENSES/CC-BY-SA-4.0.txt
    - Note: Usage of these assets is strictly subject to Section 3.

3. TRADEMARK AND IDENTITY POLICY
--------------------------------
- TRADEMARKS: "Valecium"™, the "ValeciumOS" wordmark, and the "Va" element 
  block icon are trademarks belonging to Vincent Yang. 

- SCOPE OF GRANT: The CC-BY-SA-4.0 license applies strictly to the copyright
  of the image files within `Documentation/assets/`. This grant does not
  constitute permission to use the "Valecium" name or "Va" block in any
  manner that suggests official affiliation, endorsement, or ownership.

- DERIVATIVES: Any redistribution or derivative work that deviates 
  significantly from the upstream source must be re-branded to avoid 
  user confusion and brand dilution.

4. CONTRIBUTION POLICY (DCO)
----------------------------
This project utilizes the Developer Certificate of Origin (DCO) to maintain 
legal clarity. By contributing to this project, you agree that:

- INBOUND = OUTBOUND: Your contribution is licensed under the same terms 
  as the file or directory being modified.
  
- SIGN-OFF: You certify that you have the right to submit the work. All 
  commits should include a "Signed-off-by" line in the following format:
  
      Signed-off-by: Random J Developer <random@example.com>

5. COPYRIGHT
------------
Unless explicitly noted in individual file headers:
Copyright © 2024–2026 Vincent and ValeciumOS contributors. 
All rights reserved.